{{refimprove|date=November 2010}}

'''Urban Agricultural Architecture (UAA)''' is the practice of integrating [[Organic farming|organic]], [[hydroponic]], [[aeroponic]] or [[aquaponic]] [[Agricultural science|farming technologies]] into buildings of all types.  An example can be as small as building a lean-to-[[greenhouse]] on a single-family home and using it as a [[kitchen garden]].  Examples of large-scale projects are the hydroponic greenhouses of [[Lufa Farms]], the rooftop farms of [[Brooklyn Grange]] Rooftop Farm,<ref>http://www.growingagreenerworld.com/episode322/</ref> and the vertical farms of Sky Greens.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2nFQOkzEjxQ</ref>  Building types that can incorporate food growing technologies include: single-family home, multi-family housing, mixed-use buildings, schools,<ref>http://inhabitat.com/nyc/photos-fifth-street-farm-unveils-new-rooftop-farm-designed-by-michael-arad-at-the-east-village-earth-school/</ref> restaurants,<ref>https://www.bloomberg.com/photo/rosemary-s-rooftop-farm-/218685.html</ref> institutional buildings,<ref>http://commcgi.cc.stonybrook.edu/am2/publish/General_University_News_2/rooftop_farm.shtml</ref> vertical farms, hoop houses and greenhouses that are designed to urban conditions.<ref>http://popupcity.net/top-5-of-the-greatest-urban-rooftop-farms/</ref><ref>"Vertical Farm Video". Discovery Channel. 2009-04-23. http://watch.discoverychannel.ca/daily-planet/april-2009/daily-planet-april-23-2009/#clip164926 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090510091346/http://watch.discoverychannel.ca/daily-planet/april-2009/daily-planet-april-23-2009/#clip164926 |date=2009-05-10 }}. Retrieved 2009-06-26.</ref> Existing urban buildings and structures can also be adaptively reused incorporating agricultural technologies to produce food for urban populations.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-25948880</ref><ref>Roberts, G. (2010, September 27). "Fish Farm, With a Side of Greens". New York Times.  https://www.nytimes.com/2010/09/28/business/energy-environment/28iht-rbofish.html?_r=1. Retrieved 2010-10-01.</ref>

